          <msContents>
            <summary>
              <p>10 fol. on parchment; Shelfmark Vat. ar. 1784; Qurʾānic Text: Q 73:18-75:26, Q 75:28-87:3, Q 87:7-96:3; 21 lines per page; Dimensions: 350 x 428mm; Script style <hi rend="italic">kūfī </hi>type C.Ia influenced by <hi rend="italic">ḥiǧāzī IV</hi> and the early <hi rend="italic">kūfī </hi>script style B.I; Estimated date of production: 700-800 CE. </p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>Another three fragments <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/verse-navigator/sura/3/verse/66/manuscripts/33">BnF Arabe 332</ref> from Paris, <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/verse-navigator/sura/64/verse/14/manuscripts/893">KFQ 49</ref> from the Khalili Collections in London and  fol. 1 of <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/manuscripts/892/page/1r?sura=39&amp;amp;verse=47">E 16264 D</ref> from Pennsylvania University Museum originally belonged to the same codex.</p>
              <p> </p>
              <p>In his catalogue from 1992 F. Déroche gives no estimate date of production of KFQ 49 and labels the script of the fragment as 'unclassified' (<ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/QJQEKNSJ" sameAs="QJQEKNSJ" type="zotero">See Déroche 1992: p. 129</ref>), although in his early publication about the BnF collection Déroche classifies the script of the sister fragment Arabe 332 "to be close" to C.Ia  (<ref target="https://www.zotero.org/groups/corpuscoranicum_pub/items/itemKey/KCAZQ5NS" sameAs="KCAZQ5NS" type="zotero">See Déroche 1983: p. 77</ref>). The connection of the script of the codex with early script styles such as <hi rend="italic">ḥiǧāzī IV</hi> and the <hi rend="italic">kūfī </hi>script style B.I suggest an early dating. The absence of the vocalisation and a very scarce usage of the diacritical signs also speak for an early date.</p>
              <p/>
            </summary>
