          <physDesc>
            <objectDesc>
              <supportDesc material="parchment">
                <support>
                  <p>Text division: The group of three oblique dashes mark the end of a verse. Every tenth verse is marked by a circle filled with red ink with a small dot in the center. Sūrahs were originally separated with a blank space, a later hand writes the Sūrah title and the number of verses in a cursive hand in black ink. Other sister fragments <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/verse-navigator/sura/3/verse/66/manuscripts/33">Arabe 332</ref>, <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/verse-navigator/sura/64/verse/14/manuscripts/893">KFQ 49</ref> and <ref target="https://corpuscoranicum.de/en/manuscripts/892/page/1r?sura=39&amp;verse=47">E 16264 D</ref> show the same separation of the verses and Sūrahs. The cursive hand that writes the title of the Sūrahs and the number of verses seem to be the same in the fragments.</p>
                </support>
                <extent>Folios: 10
